import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all capital cities?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    capital_cities_per_state = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    capital_cities_per_state = capital_cities_per_state.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(capital_cities_per_state['state'], capital_cities_per_state['counts'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=capital_cities_per_state['counts'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max number of capital cities')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of capital cities')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(x=data['lon'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean longitude: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axhline(y=data['lat'].mean(), color='green', label=f"Mean latitude: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Longitude")
    plt.ylabel("Latitude")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    states = data['state'].unique()
    colors = plt.cm.tab20.colors[:len(states)]
    for i, state in enumerate(states):
        state_data = data[data['state'] == state]
        ax.scatter(state_data['lon'], state_data['lat'], color=colors[i], label=state)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude within each state?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.regplot(x='lon', y='lat', data=data, scatter_kws={'s': 50}, line_kws={'color': 'red'})
    plt.title('What is the relationship between longitude and latitude of capital cities?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
